items.title: Fara-7B: An Efficient Agentic Model for Computer Use
items.summary: Fara-7B is our first agentic small language model for computer use . This experimental model includes robust safety measures to aid responsible deployment . Despite its size, Fara 7B holds its own against larger, more resource-intensive agentic systems . Microsoft Research: Fara7B: An Efficient Agentic Model for Computer Use .

items.title: Microsoft’s Fara-7B is a computer-use AI agent that rivals GPT-4o and works directly on your PC
items.summary: Fara-7B is designed to navigate user interfaces using the same tools a human does: a mouse and keyboard . The model operates by visually perceiving a web page through screenshots and predicting specific coordinates for actions like clicking, typing, and scrolling . Microsoft says the model is small enough to run locally, it allows users to automate sensitive workflows without that information ever leaving the device .

items.title: Lean4: How the theorem prover works and why it's the new competitive edge in AI
items.summary: Lean4 is an open-source programming language and interactive theorem prover . Lean4 promises to make AI safer, more secure and deterministic in its functionality . It enables us to turn an AI’s claim (“I found a solution”) into a formally checkable proof that is indeed correct . Anyone can independently check a Lean4 proof, and the outcome will be the same – a stark contrast to the opaque reasoning of neural networks .

items.title: OpenAI is ending API access to fan-favorite GPT-4o model in February 2026
items.summary: OpenAI has sent out emails notifying API customers that its chatgpt-4o-latest model will be retired from the developer platform in mid-February 2026 . The planned retirement marks a shift for a model that, upon its release, was both a technical milestone and a cultural phenomenon within the OpenAI’s ecosystem .

items.title: Salesforce Agentforce Observability lets you watch your AI agents think in near-real time
items.summary: Salesforce launched a suite of monitoring tools designed to track AI agents making decisions . The company says businesses have increased AI implementation by 282% recently . The tools give organizations granular visibility into every action their AI agents take, every reasoning step they follow, and every guardrail they trigger . The move comes as businesses grapple with a fundamental tension in AI adoption .

items.title: Google’s ‘Nested Learning’ paradigm could solve AI's memory and continual learning problem
items.summary: Researchers at Google have developed a new AI paradigm aimed at solving one of the biggest limitations in today’s large language models . Nested Learning reframes a model and its training as a system of nested, multi-level optimization problems . The researchers argue that this approach can unlock more expressive learning algorithms, leading to better in-context learning and memory .
